com.poesys.accounting.db.account

Class AbstractDistributionAccountProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
      • com.poesys.accounting.db.account.AbstractDistributionAccountProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAccount, IDistributionAccount, com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DistributionAccountProxy

    public abstract class AbstractDistributionAccountProxy
extends com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
implements IDistributionAccount

    A data-access layer data-transfer object (DTO) lazy-loading proxy for the DistributionAccount. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
